Class StackCalculatorTemplate<T>

java.lang.Object
ru.nsu.fit.tsukanov.calculator.template.stack.StackCalculatorTemplate<T>

Calculator<T>
Direct Known Subclasses:
CodingCalculator, StackCalculatorInstance
public class StackCalculatorTemplate<T> extends Object implements Calculator<T>
Complex number calculator. Calculates different operations. Template for Calculator. Use prefix notation for input string (or tokens).

    • next

      public boolean next() throws CalculatorException
      Calculates next token. It's useful to use this after toke appending.
      Returns:
      true if next next will do nothing. In correct state it signalized that result was calculated. So check result
      Throws:
      CalculatorException - if there is some exception to parsing of calculating, or bad input.
